title: For Sale:  1943 Smith and Wesson Victory .38 spl.
postcontent: This Victory Model was sold thru the Defense Supply Corp. to the Houston Shipyards , Houston TX. They built Liberty ships for the US during WWII. The letter from Smith and wesson states this.  Shipped on Dec. 16  1943, it retains  over 95% of the original mid-night black finish. The finish is thinning a bit on the front strap. All parts are matching numbers except the grips. Bore is bright and has strong lands and grooves. The gun does not seem to have been shot much as the cyl. locks up tight and the case hardening remains on the trigger and hammer, A VERY nice example . Houston Ship Builders built at least 47 Liberty ships during the war. The names of many or the ships were historic people in Texas such as :  Sam Houston , Davy Crocket , Houston Volunteers , Amelia Earhart , James Bowie , James Madison, and Steven F Austin , and many others.( see pictures ). Smith and Wesson says...  " A very small group of the Victory Models were sold to commercial companies and police agencies during the war time production. "  This is one of those.  A great piece of US history , in my opinion. $35 covers shipping and transfer to your FFL of C&R.
